-- Spain’s Abengoa to Invest $114.3 Million in Peruvian Power Line
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2013-02-21T19:17:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-21/spain-s-abengoa-to-invest-114-3-million-in-peruvian-power-line.html
Abengoa SA (ABG)  of Spain won a concession
to build a power line in Peru, the Andean country’s government
said.  The company will invest $114.3 million over the next 38
months in the 220-kilovolt, 354-kilometer (212-mile) Machu
Picchu-Tintaya transmission line, state investment agency
Proinversion said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
